WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.203
Start in CRM, on Vehicles.

p02
00:00:02.550 --> 00:00:09.086
Read the top band before you open anyone's account.

p03
00:00:09.312 --> 00:00:10.287
Nearly four thousand vehicles on file, and fourteen flagged.

p04
00:00:10.525 --> 00:00:11.903
Fourteen. Across the whole network.

p05
00:00:12.142 --> 00:00:16.047
That tells you this ticket is almost certainly one member, not a wave.

p06
00:00:16.257 --> 00:00:21.232
So work the funnel in order: the account, the plate, the blocklist, the hardware.

p07
00:00:21.680 --> 00:00:24.982
Open the member from the customer list and go to the Membership tab.

p08
00:00:25.715 --> 00:00:27.949
Three blocks answer most of these tickets.

p09
00:00:28.469 --> 00:00:30.588
Loyalty and points holds the barcode.

p10
00:00:30.856 --> 00:00:33.422
That is the code the P-O-S actually reads.

p11
00:00:33.883 --> 00:00:36.260
Plan details tells you the status is active.

p12
00:00:36.774 --> 00:00:40.762
Billing cycle tells you the next charge, so the plan is not past due.

p13
00:00:41.381 --> 00:00:44.080
Any of those fails, and you already have your answer.

p14
00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:45.625
Now the header chips.

p15
00:00:46.332 --> 00:00:48.264
Plate linked is the one that matters here.

p16
00:00:48.795 --> 00:00:51.234
It says a plate is on file for the cameras.

p17
00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:55.548
Open the Vehicles tab and read what is actually on the account.

p18
00:00:56.138 --> 00:00:59.971
No chip, or the wrong plate, and the gate has nothing to match.

p19
00:01:00.309 --> 00:01:01.802
Do not add a vehicle.

p20
00:01:02.126 --> 00:01:05.133
You report the gap. You never fill it from the demo.

p21
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.142
Back out to CRM Vehicles and search the exact plate.

p22
00:01:09.884 --> 00:01:14.951
The master list is the plate's own record:

p23
00:01:15.282 --> 00:01:18.617
license plate, make and model, year, customer, location, status, last visit.

p24
00:01:19.206 --> 00:01:20.551
Confirm three things.

p25
00:01:20.892 --> 00:01:23.085
Right customer. A sane status. A last visit that matches the member's story.

p26
00:01:23.446 --> 00:01:25.896
One caution from today's capture: the list returned a fetch error.

p27
00:01:26.631 --> 00:01:35.200
Make sure rows actually loaded before you say a plate is not on file.

p28
00:01:35.600 --> 00:01:36.814
Now the blocklist. Settings, Users and Security, Blacklisted.

p29
00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:39.504
Four columns: plate, terminal, created by, created.

p30
00:01:39.812 --> 00:01:40.681
A plate on this list is refused at the gate no matter how healthy the membership looks.

p31
00:01:41.500 --> 00:01:45.496
So a clean account with a won't-scan symptom sends you straight here.

p32
00:01:46.006 --> 00:01:48.522
Read it and leave it alone.

p33
00:01:48.858 --> 00:02:02.000
Adding or removing a blacklisted plate from the demo is forbidden.

p34
00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:04.184
Both clean? Then it's the site.

p35
00:02:04.184 --> 00:02:06.541
Open IT and Support, then System Alerts.

p36
00:02:06.541 --> 00:02:10.506
A tunnel or P-O-S fault at the member's location would surface here.

p37
00:02:10.506 --> 00:02:13.706
In today's corpus the page would not load at all.

p38
00:02:13.706 --> 00:02:17.793
If it is still down when you get there, hold the parked card

p39
00:02:17.793 --> 00:02:20.469
and route the hardware question to the site team.

p40
00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:23.727
Still in IT and Support, open the Support Queue.

p41
00:02:24.356 --> 00:02:26.630
You want an open ticket at the member's home site.

p42
00:02:26.944 --> 00:02:31.445
Today's capture has one: an L-P-R ticket at Miami North, high priority.

p43
00:02:32.225 --> 00:02:34.348
L-P-R is the plate-reading hardware.

p44
00:02:34.680 --> 00:02:36.941
An open ticket there changes your whole read.

p45
00:02:37.291 --> 00:02:41.279
This stops being one member and becomes an attachment to a known site issue.

p46
00:02:41.749 --> 00:02:42.667
One last stop, and it's a quiet one.

p47
00:02:42.867 --> 00:02:45.923
Settings, Operations, Cancellation Reasons.

p48
00:02:46.152 --> 00:02:47.458
The migrated reason set includes R-F-I-D tag issues, not reading.

p49
00:02:47.909 --> 00:02:52.767
That is a recognized failure mode,

p50
00:02:52.981 --> 00:02:58.786
and naming it tells the next team exactly what the field already knows.

p51
00:02:59.029 --> 00:03:01.156
Confirm the wording against the live list.

p52
00:03:01.448 --> 00:03:03.840
The rows did not load in today's capture.

p53
00:03:04.240 --> 00:03:05.454
Now build the ticket.

p54
00:03:06.038 --> 00:03:08.213
State which checks passed and which failed.

p55
00:03:08.754 --> 00:03:11.336
Barcode present, plan active, or not.

p56
00:03:11.886 --> 00:03:13.214
Plate linked, or not. The master-list status.

p57
00:03:13.762 --> 00:03:15.081
Whether the plate appears on Blacklisted.

p58
00:03:15.414 --> 00:03:17.257
Any open L-P-R ticket or system alert at the site.

p59
00:03:17.870 --> 00:03:20.675
Tag the R-F-I-D reason when it fits, and name the location.

p60
00:03:21.184 --> 00:03:24.463
The fix happens in production with the right role.

p61
00:03:25.056 --> 00:03:31.642
A relink, a blocklist removal, a dispatch. Never here.

p62
00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:33.372
That's the funnel.

p63
00:03:33.372 --> 00:03:35.374
Frame it on the vehicle list.

p64
00:03:35.374 --> 00:03:38.013
Read the barcode, the status, and the next charge.

p65
00:03:38.013 --> 00:03:42.374
Confirm the plate is linked, find it in the master list, check the blocklist,

p66
00:03:42.374 --> 00:03:45.307
then work the hardware trail through alerts and the queue.

p67
00:03:45.307 --> 00:03:47.067
Most tickets never reach the bottom.

p68
00:03:47.067 --> 00:03:49.678
And you changed nothing on the way down.

